onflict of Forsyth County, Georgia]]\n*[[Exodusters]]\n*[[Historical racial and ethnic demographics of the United States]]\n*[[White flight]]\n*[[Living for the City]]\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/28/science/african-american-dna.html Carl Zimmer, \"Tales of African-American History Found in DNA\"], ''New York Times'', 27 May 2016\n* {{cite book |last=Arnesen |first=Eric |title=Black Protest and the Great Migration: A Brief History with Documents |year=2002 |location=Bedford |publisher=St. Martin's Press |isbn=0-312-39129-3}}\n* Baldwin, Davarian L. ''Chicago's New Negroes: Modernity, the Great Migration, & Black Urban Life'' (Univ of North Carolina Press, 2007)\n* DeSantis, Alan D. \"Selling the American dream myth to black southerners: The Chicago Defender and the Great Migration of 1915\u20131919.\" ''Western Journal of Communication'' (1998) 62#4 pp: 474\u2013511. [http://www.uky.edu/~addesa01/documents/SellingtheAmericanDreamMyth.pdf online]\n* {{cite book |last=Dove |first=Rita |authorlink=Rita Dove |title=Thomas and Beulah |year=1986 |publisher=Carnegie Mellon University Press |isbn=0-88748-021-7|title-link=Thomas and Beulah }}\n* {{cite book |last=Gregory |first= James N. |title=The Southern Diaspora: How the Great Migrations of Black and White Southerners Transformed America |location=Chapel Hill |year=2007 |publisher=University of North Carolina Press |isbn=978-0-8078-5651-2}}\n* {{cite book |last=Grossman |first=James R. |title=Land of Hope: Chicago, Black Southerners, and the Great Migration |year=1991 |location=Chicago |publisher=University of Chicago Press |isbn=0-226-30995-9 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/landofhope00jame }}\n* Holley, Donald. ''The Second Great Emancipation: The Mechanical Cotton Picker, Black Migration, and How They Shaped the Modern South'' (University of Arkansas Press, 2000)\n* {{cite book |last=Lemann |first=Nicholas |title=The Promise